msgctxt "sn52.5:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 52 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 52 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.5:0.2"
msgid "1. Rahogatavagga "
msgstr "1. In Private "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn52.5:0.3"
msgid "5. Dutiyakaṇḍakīsutta "
msgstr "5. At Thorny Wood (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn52.5:1.1"
msgid "Sāketanidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāketa. "

msgctxt "sn52.5:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Sāriputta said to Anuruddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.5:1.3"
msgid "“asekhenāvuso anuruddha, bhikkhunā katame dhammā upasampajja vihātabbā”ti? "
msgstr "“Reverend Anuruddha, what things should a mendicant who is an adept enter and remain in?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.5:1.4"
msgid "“Asekhenāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā cattāro satipaṭṭhānā upasampajja vihātabbā. "
msgstr "“Reverend Sāriputta, a mendicant who is an adept should enter and remain in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation. "

msgctxt "sn52.5:1.5"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn52.5:1.6"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn52.5:1.7"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn52.5:1.8"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn52.5:1.9"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ—"
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn52.5:1.10"
msgid "asekhenāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā ime cattāro satipaṭṭhānā upasampajja vihātabbā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant who is an adept should enter and remain in these four kinds of mindfulness meditation.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn52.5:1.11"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

